<span id="freeTextContainer7261389513457791691">DNF. BUT I loved it. The whole story is in the train of thought of a young soldier going off to fight in the civil war. Starting with dreams of glory and patriotism. Yet fearful and self doubting. That this was written in &apos;stream of consciousness&apos; was itself masterful: by a writer who had never been to war was hugely staggering and was probably (I did a little research here) the first book written of this kind.<br/>Incredible.</span>
