<span id="freeTextContainer7663761076085796912"><i>Librarian Note: There is more than one author by this name in the Goodreads database.</i><br/><br/>Stephen Crane was an American novelist, poet and journalist, best known for the novel <i>The Red Badge of Courage</i>. That work introduced the reading world to Crane&apos;s striking prose, a mix of impressionism, naturalism and symbolism. He died at age 28 in Badenweiler, Baden, Germany.</span>
  <span id="freeText7663761076085796912" style="display:none"><i>Librarian Note: There is more than one author by this name in the Goodreads database.</i><br /><br />Stephen Crane was an American novelist, poet and journalist, best known for the novel <i>The Red Badge of Courage</i>. That work introduced the reading world to Crane's striking prose, a mix of impressionism, naturalism and symbolism. He died at age 28 in Badenweiler, Baden, Germany.</span>
